@startuml
title Slides Cache and Follow Trainer
hide footbox
autonumber

skinparam BackgroundColor transparent
skinparam SequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam ParticipantPadding 20
skinparam BoxPadding 10
skinparam MaxMessageSize 110
skinparam WrapWidth 220
skinparam RoundCorner 8

actor "Participant browser\nstatic/participant.js" as Participant
participant "Railway slides HTTP + WS" as Railway
participant "Daemon slides API\nslides/router.py" as SlidesAPI
participant "Daemon main loop + SlidesRunner" as Loop
participant "Addons bridge\nPowerPoint events" as Addons
database "Railway PDF cache" as Cache
participant "Google Drive" as Drive

group Catalog bootstrap (daemon startup)
Loop -> Loop: load slides catalog from disk\nmark all slugs as not_cached
Loop -> SlidesAPI: populate misc_state.slides_catalog
end

group Cache probe on WS (re)connect
Loop -> Railway: HEAD /api/slides/download/{slug}\nfor each catalog slug
Railway -> Cache: check cached PDF presence
Railway --> Loop: cached or not_cached
Loop -> SlidesAPI: update slides_cache_status
SlidesAPI -> Railway: broadcast slides_cache_status

Participant -> Railway: GET /{session}/api/slides
Railway -> SlidesAPI: proxy daemon list request
SlidesAPI --> Railway: slides with embedded cache status
Railway --> Participant: normalized catalog
end

group Participant opens a slide
Participant -> Railway: GET /{session}/api/slides/check/{slug}
Railway -> SlidesAPI: proxy check request

alt Already cached (trusted from WS-connect probe)
  SlidesAPI --> Railway: 200 cached
else Cache miss
  SlidesAPI -> SlidesAPI: mark status=downloading
  SlidesAPI -> Railway: broadcast slides_cache_status
  SlidesAPI -> Railway: POST /api/slides/download-from-gdrive/{slug}\n(REST, blocks until done)
  Railway -> Drive: download PDF
  Drive --> Railway: PDF bytes
  Railway -> Cache: store cached PDF
  Railway --> SlidesAPI: {sha256, size, status: cached}
  SlidesAPI -> SlidesAPI: mark status=cached\nstore last_sha256
  SlidesAPI -> Railway: broadcast slides_cache_status
  SlidesAPI --> Railway: 200 cached
end

Participant -> Railway: GET /{session}/api/slides/download/{slug}
Railway -> Cache: serve inline PDF with ETag / Last-Modified
Railway --> Participant: PDF document
end

group PPTX updated — daemon retries until Google Drive publishes new PDF
Loop -> Loop: scan PPTX files every ~10s\ndetect mtime change
Loop -> Loop: start background redownload\npoller thread for slug

loop up to 5 retries, 5s apart (daemon thread)
  Loop -> Railway: POST /api/slides/download-from-gdrive/{slug}
  Railway -> Drive: download PDF
  Drive --> Railway: PDF bytes
  Railway -> Cache: store PDF
  Railway --> Loop: {sha256, size}
  Loop -> Loop: compare SHA256 hash\nwith stored last_sha256
  alt Hash changed — new version available
    Loop -> SlidesAPI: mark status=cached\nstore new last_sha256
    SlidesAPI -> Railway: broadcast slides_cache_status\nwith refreshed_slugs=[slug]
    Railway --> Participant: slides_cache_status event
  else Hash unchanged — Google Drive not ready yet
    Loop -> Loop: wait 5s before next attempt
  end
end

alt All retries exhausted
  Loop -> Loop: log warning + beep\n(gdrive_pdf_not_updated)
end

alt Participant is displaying the refreshed slide
  Participant -> Participant: detect refreshed_slugs\nincludes active slide
  Participant -> Railway: GET /{session}/api/slides/check/{slug}
  Railway --> Participant: 200 cached (already fresh)
  Participant -> Railway: GET /{session}/api/slides/download/{slug}
  Railway --> Participant: refreshed PDF
end
end

group Follow trainer from live PowerPoint
Addons -> Loop: slide {deck, slide, presenting}
Loop -> Loop: map presentation name to catalog slug + participant URL
Loop -> Railway: broadcast slides_current {slug, url, current_page}
Railway -> Railway: mirror slides_current in server state
Railway --> Participant: slides_current event
Participant -> Participant: if follow is enabled,\nopen overlay and jump to the host page
end
@enduml
